The code for this server was written by Douglas Eck, is open source,
and was originally built as a front end for the music collection used
at University of Montreal for the Search Inside the Music project at
Sun Labs, Boston.

Contributors:

Douglas Eck
 - "The whole shebang" as Ron Weiss politely put it.
   More explicitly: initial implementation of this system as part of Search Inside the Music (SITM)

Michael Mandel 
 - playdar resolver

Ron Weiss
 - documentation and cleanup in preparation for initial open source release

Gordon (built on SITM) was further developed at New York University,
Steinhardt as part of the IMSL project whithin the MARL research group (NYU-Columbia)

